==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French [[paienime]], from ecclesiastical Latin [[paganismus]] ‘paganism’, from Latin [[paganus]] ‘pagan’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'peɪnɪm/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|paynim|paynims}}
# a [[pagan]] or [[heathen]], especially a [[Muslim]]
#:*'''1964''': St Helen’s bell rang reminders that she lived, a '''paynim''' or Mahometan, in the church’s shadow. — Anthony Burgess, ''Nothing Like The Sun''